    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/233">Berengarius</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/234">Adelbertus</persName> divina
                        providente clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">reges</rs>. Si sacris ac
                        venerabilibus locis temporalia atque transitoria concedimus, magnam apud
                        Dominum remunerari in futuro nequaquam diffidimus. Quocirca noverit omnium
                        fidelium sanctae Dei Aecclesiae nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac
                        futurorum industria, <persName key="#Intercessory #Bishops"><name
                                ref="Giselbrandus">Giseprandum</name></persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/239">sanctae <placeName ref="#places/627"
                                >Terdonensis</placeName> aecclesiae</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopum</rs> nec non <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Bishops" ref="#people/1303">Vuidonem</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/96">sanctae <placeName ref="#places/38"
                                >Mutinensis</placeName> sedis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">presulem</rs> humiliter nostram <rs key="#Intercessory"
                            >exorasse</rs> celsitudinem, quatenus ut amorae supernae remuneracionis
                        per nostri precepti paginam quoddam <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        infra civitatem <placeName ref="#places/43">Placentinam</placeName> a beate
                        videlicet memoriae <persName key="#Queen" ref="#people/55"
                            >Angelberga</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatricae</rs> constructum et <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/53"
                            key="#Cartula #Houses #Rivers #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Mountains #Curtes #Forests #Fisheries #Mills #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Castle #Local_markets #Periodic_markets #Public_exactions #Districtio #Churches #Cells/hermitages #Abbesses #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            >in honore sancti Sisti hedificatum</orgName>
                        <persName key="#Abbesses #auntOf" ref="#people/67">Bertae</persName>
                        gloriosissimae <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatissae</rs>
                        <rs key="#auntOf">amitae</rs> nostrae cum omnibus suis pertinenciis
                        confirmare ac corroborare dignaremur, simul quoque roborantes et in
                        perpetuum concedentes eidem monasterio quasdam <rs key="#Curtes"
                        >cortes</rs>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/40"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Vuardistalla</placeName></geogName> scilicet,
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/110"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Campum Miliatio</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/207"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Curte Nova</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/42"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Piguniarius</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/112"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Sexto</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/38"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Lutiariam</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/77"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Littora Paludiana</placeName></geogName>, <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/80"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/33">Villolae</placeName></geogName>, cum adiacenciis eorum et omnia
                        quecumque memorata imperatrix institutionis suae iudicati ubicumque eidem
                        caenobio diffinivit ad habendum. Quorum petitionibus tota devotione
                        faventes, id fieri annuimus, hoc nostrum preceptum scribi iubentes, per quod
                        prelibatae Bertae abbatissae eundem monasterium confirmamus ac corroboramus,
                        quatenus in sua sit potestate et dominio quousque vixerit et ibidem
                        dominatrix et ordinatrix atque rectrix invigilet ac permaneat donec eius
                        fuerit vita. Per quod etiam iam prescripto venerabili loco concedimus et
                        confirmamus omnes res et possessiones mobiles ac immobiles, tam per <rs
                            key="#Cartula">cartulas</rs> quamque extra cartulas vel cuiuscumque
                        inscriptionis titulo ad partem ipsius monasterii legibus adquisitas et
                        adquirendas, seu quicquid per egum vel imperatorum antecessorum nostrorum
                        precepta ad eundem sacrum locum collatum; atque <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellulam</rs> quandam que antiquitus Monasterium dicebatur non procul a
                        Placentinae urbe sitam, loco qui Capud Trebiae vocatur, in qua <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1503"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >apostolorum principis dicata</orgName> consistit, cum omnibus inibi
                        pertinentibus, quemadmodum <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/80"
                            >Carlemannus</persName> serenissimus <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>
                        antiquitus eandem cellulam cum universis suis appenditiis et pertinentiis
                        eidem monasterio <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure"
                            >proprietario iure</rs> largitus est, prenominato venerabili loco per
                        hoc nostrae regalis auctoritatis preceptum ex integro perdonamus, largimur,
                        confirmamus, modisque omnibus corrobor[mu]s. <rs key="#Personal_statuses"
                            >Familias quoque utriusque sexus et conditiones</rs> cum <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs> et <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs>
                        earumque appenditiis, cum omnibus <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Houses">casis</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Cereals">campis</rs>, pascuis, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, salectis, sationibus, <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis
                            aquarumque decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>,
                        fluminibus, <rs key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>, ripis, rupinis, <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montibus</rs>, collibus, vallibus ac planiciebus,
                        coltis et incoltis, divisis et indivisis, <rs
                            key="#Local_markets #Periodic_markets">mercationibus</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Public_exactions">vectigalibus</rs>, <rs key="#Districtio"
                            >districtionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs>,
                            <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldiis et aldianis</rs> et cum omnibus ad eundem
                        monasterium iuxste et legaliter respicientibus in integrum confirmamus, ita
                        videlicet, ut pelibata abbatissa Berta, quousque vixerit, hac nostra
                        auctoritate roborata de prescriptis rebus eidem monasterio pertinentibus tam
                        per preceptorum paginam, ut diximus, quamque aliarum instrumenta cartarum et
                        adquisitis et adquirendis potestative omnium faciat magnarum parvarumque
                        personarum molestatione remota. Si quis vero hanc nostram auctoritatem
                        violare temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">centum quinquaginta libras auri
                            optimi</rs> componere coga[t]ur, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem
                            ka[m]erae nostrae</rs> et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities"
                            >medietatem sepe fate Bertae abbatissae</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur
                        diligentiusque ab omnibus observetur, manibus propriis roborantes de anulo
                        nostro iussimus insigniri. Signa domnorum (MF) (MF) Berengarii et Adelberti
                        serenissimorum regum. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Hubertus"
                                >Ubertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Bruningus"
                            >Bruningi</name></persName> episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovit et subscripsit. (SR) (SI D). Data XVI
                        kalendis februarii, anno dominicae incarnationis DCCCCL, regni vero domni
                        Berengarii atque Adelberti piissimorum regum primo, indictione nona. Actum
                            <placeName ref="#places/65">Papiae Titinum</placeName>. Feliciter,
                        amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
